cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.CR 

The paper discusses methods for generating conditional probability tables (CPTs) for Bayesian networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) applications. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions case studies on military effects and burnt forest desertification, which suggest that the paper may fall under the sub-categories of cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.CE (computational engineering, finance, and science). Finally, the paper introduces new quality measures for determining the goodness of a CPT and for comparing CPTs with each other, which may suggest that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (cryptography and security).
